<%- include('partials/header') %>
<div class="container my-5">
  <h1>Microsoft Purview — Knowledge</h1>
  <p class="text-muted">A short, non-technical introduction to Microsoft Purview and how it maps to our site operations.</p>

  <div id="kpiRow" class="row g-3 my-4">
    <!-- KPI cards will be injected by client script -->
  </div>

  <section class="my-4">
    <h3>What is Microsoft Purview?</h3>
    <p>Microsoft Purview is a data governance solution. It offers cataloging, classification and policy controls to help organizations understand and govern their data.</p>
    <h4>How this maps to Panda</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Catalog/Inventory → media &amp; posts metadata (our <code>media.tags</code> and post metadata)</li>
      <li>Classifications → content tags, sensitivity labels (mapped to internal tag fields)</li>
      <li>Retention → retention policies documented in the Admin guides</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="my-4">
    <h3>Glossary</h3>
    <dl>
      <dt>Catalog</dt><dd>Inventory of data sources and assets.</dd>
      <dt>Classification</dt><dd>Labels applied to assets (e.g., public, internal, restricted).</dd>
      <dt>Lineage</dt><dd>How data flows between systems.</dd>
    </dl>
  </section>

  <script src="/js/purview.js" nonce="<%= cspNonce %>"></script>
</div>
